    "Subsequently, a detailed description of the forward diffusion process is presented.",
    "Furthermore, this section provides comprehensive insights into our model's training and optimization process, culminating with a detailed explanation of how to extrapolate our denoising model.",
    "For the SISR task, a high-resolution (HR) image dataset and its corresponding low-resolution (LR) counterpart are combined to create a paired dataset D = {x i, y i } N i=1, representing samples obtained from a distribution p(y|x) with unknown properties.",
    "This dataset has an ill-posed mapping between LR and HR images, meaning that a single low-resolution source image x may correspond to multiple high-resolution target y.",
    "Our objective is to acquire the capability to generate high-resolution images that closely match distribution p(y|x), given a lowresolution image as input."
